The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump during a visit to Flavor First Growers and Packers in Mills River, North Carolina. The President thanked the farmers and business people he met and criticized the governor for not allowing him to visit sooner due to COVID-19 restrictions. He praised the success of the Farmers to Families Food Box program, which provides food to families in need during the pandemic, and announced an additional $1 billion in funding for the program. Secretary of Agriculture Sonny Perdue and Ivanka Trump also spoke about the program and its impact. The President also discussed the economy, job numbers, and his administration's efforts to support farmers and cut regulations. He encouraged North Carolinians to vote for him in the upcoming election.